So we already noticed that in the beginning, the promotional material was a bit careful

00:54:41.820 --> 00:54:46.379
with what kind of size of data set it would be beneficial from.

00:54:46.379 --> 00:54:50.139
And it turned out from the test that we were doing that it's quite quickly already.

00:54:50.139 --> 00:54:56.360
Because data needs to be transferred to the GPU, you get a small overhead.

00:54:56.360 --> 00:54:59.580
So you start seeing the difference when the data set size grows.

00:54:59.580 --> 00:55:03.979
But it's already from one gigabyte and up, so it's relatively quickly because most data

00:55:04.060 --> 00:55:09.459
that you would work with in a professional setting usually tends to grow a lot.

